label.value: regulation of neutrophil apoptotic process

label.value: positive regulation of neutrophil apoptotic process

label.value: T cell differentiation in thymus

value.value: The process in which a precursor cell type acquires the specialized features of a T cell via a differentiation pathway dependent upon transit through the thymus.

definition.value: Note that immunologists typically use the word 'development' to refer to cells of B or T cell lineages undergoing the process that GO describes as 'cell differentiation'.

label.value: V(D)J recombination

value.value: The process in which immune receptor V, D, and J, or V and J gene segments, depending on the specific receptor, are recombined within a single locus utilizing the conserved heptamer and nonomer recombination signal sequences (RSS).

label.value: immunoglobulin V(D)J recombination

value.value: The process in which immunoglobulin gene segments are recombined within a single locus utilizing the conserved heptamer and nonomer recombination signal sequences (RSS). For immunoglobulin heavy chains V, D, and J gene segments are joined, and for immunoglobulin light chains V and J gene segments are joined.

label.value: T cell receptor V(D)J recombination

value.value: The process in which T cell receptor V, D, and J, or V and J gene segments, depending on the specific locus, are recombined within a single locus utilizing the conserved heptamer and nonomer recombination signal sequences (RSS).

label.value: regulation of intracellular protein transport

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of proteins within cells.

label.value: melanosome membrane

value.value: The lipid bilayer surrounding a melanosome.

label.value: response to ATP

value.value: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an ATP (adenosine 5'-triphosphate) stimulus.

label.value: meiotic cytokinesis

value.value: A cell cycle process that results in the division of the cytoplasm of a cell after meiosis, resulting in the separation of the original cell into two daughter cells.

label.value: iron import into cell

value.value: The directed movement of iron ions from outside of a cell into the cytoplasmic compartment. This may occur via transport across the plasma membrane or via endocytosis.

label.value: amide binding

value.value: Binding to an amide, any derivative of an oxoacid in which an acidic hydroxy group has been replaced by an amino or substituted amino group.

label.value: negative regulation of amine metabolic process

label.value: positive regulation of amine metabolic process

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving amines.

label.value: regulation of amine catabolic process

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways leading to the breakdown of amines.
